data.title: Faculty and Staff
data.text:
Shelley Bessey -Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies

Shelly began her journey at Keyano College in August 2018 as an instructor in the Nursing department. Shelley received her RN in 1990 and furthered her education with her undergraduate in nursing in 2013. In 2016, Shelley received a Master of Nursing from the University of Saskatchewan. She has many years’ experience as a clinical nurse focusing on critical care areas and management. She has been teaching the Collaborative Nursing program at the University of Alberta for over ten years.

Abby Boychuk - Instructor/Health Care Aide Coordinator Melissa Brown - Instructor, Prehospital Care Jennifer Courtney - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies

Maddie Dodge - Instructor, Prehospital Care

Sarah Espejo - Instructor, Prehospital Care Sarah joined the Keyano College faculty in 2023 as a Pre-hospital Medicine Instructor. Sarah received her Respiratory Therapist diploma from the College of the North Atlantic in St. John’s, NL, in 2008. Sarah and her husband have made Fort McMurray their home, together, for the last 15 years.

Sarah has a vast variety of experience working in all units of our local hospital, as well as, experience providing oxygen and sleep services within Central and Northern Alberta. Sarah has loved teaching fellow RTs, nurses, physicians, PCP/ACPs, patients and their family members over the course of her career. She comes with the goal to pass on her acquired experience & knowledge to the students of Keyano College. Sharon Grantham - Instructor/PN Program Coordinator, Nursing & Allied Health Studies

Carla Hambley - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies

Kayla Hayter - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies

Kayla joined the Keyano College faculty in 2017 as a contract nursing instructor and accepted a faculty position in 2022. Kayla received her Practical Nursing diploma from the Centre for Nursing Studies in St. John’s, NL, in 2005 and is currently teaching in the Practical Nursing Program.

Kayla has nearly two decades of experience in the acute Medicine unit at our local hospital, bringing a broad knowledge base to the Health & Human Services Department. Kayla brings a passion for nursing with her goal to pass on acquired experience & knowledge to the student population.

Trisha Holland - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies Chelsea Hynes - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies

Chelsea joined the Keyano College faculty in 2022 and is an instructor in the Bachelor of Science in Nursing program. She received her Bachelor of Nursing degree from Memorial University of Newfoundland in 2013 and has spent most of her career working in both rural & urban Manitoba. Chelsea also completed the Winnipeg Critical Care Nursing Education Program in 2015.

Chelsea has a nursing background in acute medical/surgical adult intensive & critical care, cardiac critical care, pediatrics and management. Chelsea has experience in leadership & mentorship and has passion for education.

Dr. Mehri Karimi-Dehkordi - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies Dr. Mehri Karimi-Dehkordi has extensive experience in nursing practice and teaching, particularly in cardiac critical care, equipping her to connect theoretical concepts with practical applications effectively. She possesses a genuine passion for teaching and authentically prioritizes the success of her students, demonstrating a robust dedication to preparing upcoming nurses with crucial critical thinking and problem-solving abilities.

She received her Ph.D. in 2017 from the University of Alberta and undertook her postdoctoral fellowships at three universities: the University of Ottawa, the University of Calgary, and the University of Alberta, respectively. She actively engages in research activities, publishing articles in high-impact journals and presenting at conferences and serves as both an inspiration and a mentor to students, encouraging them to pursue research opportunities. Her research interests encompass patients' values, the delivery of person-centred care, the promotion of well-being among older adults, the improvement of self-care practices, leadership dynamics within healthcare settings, and the development of effective teaching and learning methodologies.

Dr. Mehri Karimi-Dehkordi continues to be devoted to advancing nursing knowledge and nurturing the next generation of healthcare professionals. Samantha Ledrew - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies Fatima Legrou - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies

Kerry McCann - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies Dr. Natalie McMullin - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies

Dr. Natalie McMullin has almost 10 years of experience as an instructor at Keyano College in the Nursing & Allied Health Department. She received her Bachelor of Science in Nursing with Distinction in 2009. She furthered her education with her Master of Nursing degree in 2012 with her research focused on a quantitative study on breastfeeding. In 2020, Dr. McMullin received her Doctoral of Education focusing on nursing student resiliency in clinical settings. Natalie is passionate about community health nursing. When she is not working, she is spending time in the community with her husband and two sons. Renee Mouland - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies Renee Mouland graduated with Academic Excellence from the Salvation Army Grace General Hospital's School of Nursing in 1992, in St. John’s, NL. Originally from Newfoundland, Renee and her husband have made Fort McMurray their home for the last 22 + years, committing to the community and raising their family here.

She has been blessed to have had such rich experiences over her 32-year nursing career, working in all areas of nursing, in all health care settings, from remote and flight nursing on the coast of Labrador to OR nursing in a major trauma center.

Renee's background is primarily in Peri operative Nursing, but she has spent the last 9 years leading a team of nurses in a specialized private infusion clinic setting. She has held specialty certifications in Peri-operative and Holistic Nursing; as well as completed many courses relating to Biologic Treatments and Therapy. She is always looking to expand her knowledge base and is currently exploring courses in Neurodiversity.

She is passionate about teaching and believes it is a privilege to be able to share the knowledge and experiences she has gained, with the next generation health care professionals. Balqisa Omar - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies

Balqisa Omar, known as "Bal," joined Keyano College's faculty in January 2023. With East African roots-Somali and raised in London, Ontario, she brings a unique multicultural perspective to nursing education. Balqisa graduated from the University of New Brunswick in 2006 and is currently pursuing a master's degree in leadership education at Western University.

With 17 years of nursing experience, Balqisa holds certifications in Critical Care Nurse, Coronary Care Nurse, Clinical Nurse Educator, and certification in Leadership in Nurse Management. She has worked in various healthcare settings across Canada and spent four years as an ICU staff Nurse in Abu Dhabi, gaining insights into global healthcare practices and cultural nuances.

As a dedicated Nurse Instructor, Balqisa employs engaging teaching methods and fosters a supportive learning environment. Her commitment to high-quality education, combined with her global exposure in healthcare, allows her to bridge diverse perspectives and develop culturally aware healthcare professionals.

Heather Pelley - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies Janelle Riutta - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies Crystal Rose- Instructor/Nursing Lab Coordinator

Catharine Simpson-Szpak - Health Care Aide Program Coordinator

Catharine joined the Keyano College faculty in 2002 as a nursing instructor. She now is the Program Coordinator for the Health Care Aide program.

Catherine has a Master's in Nursing from the University of Southern Queensland. Her passion and dedication to student success continues to drive her students towards achieving their desired visions and dreams

Shana Strickland - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies

Ashleigh Thorne - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies Lindsy Trettenero - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies Manpreet Uppal - Instructor, Prehospital care Manpreet was born and raised as a first generation Canadian in northern British Columbia with Punjabi as his first language. He speaks both English and Punjabi fluently and enjoys the beauties of both cultures from movies and music to foods and traditions. He moved to Calgary, Alberta when he was 17 years of age on his own when he began to pursue a career in paramedicine. Aside from being a paramedic, he enjoys developing and selling residential investment real-estate projects as well as some venture capital portfolios and projects. The love of his life is his 6 year old daughter who he enjoys spending all of his free time with. When he can,ge loves to play basketball, soccer and enjoy rib-eye steaks on the BBQ while listening to all genres of music. He has recently learned how to play piano as well as enjoy percussion on traditional Indian hand drums called tabla.

As a instructor for the Pre-Hospital Program, his experience and passion in clinical education is delivering critical care high fidelity simulation for the pre-hospital setting as well as delivering certifications to our students for ACLS, PALS, and NRP courses. He enjoys collaborating with the amazing instructors from the nursing program to help bridge and bring dynamic patient care to the Advanced Care Paramedic (ACP) program here at Keyano College. He has experience on both urban and rural ground ambulance with great mentors along the way. He has also been fortunate enough to have a career as a flight paramedic in for both fixed wing and rotary critical care environments all over Alberta and northern British Columbia as well as a clinical educator in all fields of paramedicine. With 20 years experience he hopes to deliver the best possible education and experience to the students of the Pre-Hospital Care Program here at Keyano College. Manpreet hopes you enjoy your time here on campus and get to catch a Huskies game or two when you can! Marina Yanciw - Instructor, Nursing & Allied Health Studies

Marina grew up in southern Alberta and moved to Fort McMurray to finish high school. She then went on to take the practical nurse program at Keyano College and graduated in 2017. Before coming to work at Keyano College, Marina worked as an LPN on the Medicine unit at Northern Lights Regional Health Centre and at Northreach (HIV North Society) as an Overdose Prevention Nurse and Educator.

Marina's favorite thing about nursing is providing education, so working as an instructor at Keyano College is the perfect fit for her. In her free time, Marina loves to spend time outdoors with her daughter and husband.
